==Korean==
===Noun===
'''둔''' (dun)
# ([[屯]]) [[dune]], [[fort]], [[camp]]; cf. [[down]], [[town]], [[thin]] akin to German [[dünn]] 
# ([[鈍]]) [[dullness]]
# ([[臀]]) [[buttocks]] 

====Derived terms====
* [[둔덕]] (dundeog, dundeok) [[smooth]] [[hill]] ([[w:Complementarity|complementarity]]) 
* [[둔치]] (dunchi) [[dune]], [[sand]] [[dune]]

====Related terms====
* [[두둑]] (dudug, duduk) [[embankment]], [[levee]], [[ridge]] (of farms) 
* [[두덩]] (dudeong)  [[embankment]], [[levee]], [[ridge]] (of farms), [[swell]] (of eyes, pubes, etc.)
* [[두렁]] (dureong)  [[embankment]], [[levee]], [[ridge]] (of farms)
* [[둑]] (dug, duk) [[dike]], [[embankment]] 
* [[모래]][[톱]] (morae-tob, -top) [[sand]] [[dune]], literally "[[sand]] [[top]]"
* [[언덕]] (eondeog, eondeok) [[hill]]

===Verb===
'''둔치다''' ([[屯]]치다, dun-chida)
# To [[inhabit]]; [[fortify]], [[camp]], [[station]] 

